title: PG Wodehouse - Cocktail Time (Unabridged - Read by Jonathan Ceci
description:
Im bringing back to life another PG Wodehouse that hasn't been around much since the good old times of Demonoid.

The novel kicks off with Uncle Fred trying his hand at firing Brazil nuts from the window of the Drones Club and what do you know? the old skill still lingers. That gets him into trouble and to get things sorted out Uncle Fred does what he does best and that is assuming somebody else's identity. Ive always found that one of the elements Wodehouse was at his best at is impostors and people with false identities in general. It is a recurring theme in Jeeves novels and stories and in other of his works in general.
